      "side": 1,
      "message": "I like this too; I\u0027ve just tried doing this. In this case, we can\u0027t, because the behaviour of the formatter is idempotent. The tests require that:\n\n```\nbytes1 \u003d format(inputAst)\nreparsedAst \u003d parse(bytes1)\nbytes2 \u003d format(reparsedAst)\nbytes1 \u003d\u003d\u003d bytes2\n```\n\nUnfortunately in this case, that doesn\u0027t hold. In general, when we find cases where comments are getting lost or moved to very much the wrong place, this idempotency property fails and we get in trouble.",
